# UI & Razor Conventions

## When to Use Which CSS Framework

| Context | Framework | Notes |
|---------|-----------|-------|
| Worksheets, lessons, printable PDFs | **Tailwind CSS** | A4 page size (`w-[210mm]`, `min-h-[297mm]`), print utilities |
| Login, register, home, nav, admin | **Bootstrap** | Use Identity default UI styles; extend with Bootstrap components |

Do not mix Bootstrap utility classes into A4 printable layouts — keep print views Tailwind-only for predictable output.

## A4 Printable Page Template

```html
<!-- Tailwind A4 content page -->
<article class="mx-auto w-[210mm] min-h-[297mm] bg-white p-[20mm] print:shadow-none shadow-md">
    <header class="mb-6 border-b pb-4">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">@Model.Title</h1>
    </header>
    <section class="prose max-w-none">
        @* educational content *@
    </section>
</article>
```

Add `@media print` rules or Tailwind `print:` variants to hide nav, buttons, and chrome when printing.

## Bootstrap Application Shell

- Use `_Layout.cshtml` with Bootstrap navbar, container, and responsive grid.
- Keep Identity pages under `Areas/Identity/Pages` styled with Bootstrap (default scaffolding).
- Use semantic HTML (`main`, `nav`, `article`) and accessible labels on all form inputs.

## Razor Syntax

- Prefer Tag Helpers (`asp-page`, `asp-for`, `asp-validation-summary`) over raw HTML forms.
- Use partials (`_Partial.cshtml`) and View Components for reusable UI blocks.
- Never put business logic in `.cshtml` — only display logic and trivial formatting.

## UX Guidelines (Educational App)

- Clear visual hierarchy: title → learning objective → content → exercises.
- Generous whitespace and readable typography (16px+ body text on screen, 12pt+ on print).
- Show progress, breadcrumbs, or section labels so learners know where they are.
- Confirm destructive actions; provide success/error feedback via Bootstrap alerts or `TempData`.
